The paper deals with the problem of estimating 3D parameters for control applications, specifically Image-Based Visual Servoing. This falls under the domain of robotics and computer vision, which are covered by the cs.RO and cs.CV sub-categories. The paper also proposes a change of variables, which is a mathematical technique that is commonly used in machine learning and optimization, hence the cs.LG sub-category is also likely. Additionally, the paper presents experimental results using a real robot, which falls under the cs.ROBOTS sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the detection and tracking of 3D straight lines, which is a common problem in computer vision and is covered by the cs.CVPR sub-category.
